In England, in the seven days to 04 March, there were 35,366 new confirmed cases (62.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 February, there were 54,774 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 35% (19,408 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 09 March is 3,703,136 (6,579 cases per 100,000 population).
